msgid "\"submit\""
msgstr ""

#: src/view/05_forms.md:158 src/view/05_forms.md:365
msgid "\"Submit\""
msgstr ""

#: src/view/05_forms.md:164
msgid "The view should be pretty self-explanatory by now. Note two things:"
msgstr ""

#: src/view/05_forms.md:166
msgid ""
"Unlike in the controlled input example, we use `value` (not `prop:value`). "
"This is because we’re just setting the initial value of the input, and "
"letting the browser control its state. (We could use `prop:value` instead.)"
msgstr ""

#: src/view/05_forms.md:169
msgid ""
"We use `node_ref=...` to fill the `NodeRef`. (Older examples sometimes use "
"`_ref`. They are the same thing, but `node_ref` has better rust-analyzer "
"support.)"
msgstr ""

#: src/view/05_forms.md:172
msgid ""
"`NodeRef` is a kind of reactive smart pointer: we can use it to access the "
"underlying DOM node. Its value will be set when the element is rendered."
msgstr ""

#: src/view/05_forms.md:177 src/view/05_forms.md:339
msgid "// stop the page from reloading!\n"
msgstr ""

#: src/view/05_forms.md:180 src/view/05_forms.md:342
msgid "// here, we'll extract the value from the input\n"
msgstr ""

#: src/view/05_forms.md:183
msgid ""
"// event handlers can only fire after the view\n"
"        // is mounted to the DOM, so the `NodeRef` will be `Some`\n"
msgstr ""

#: src/view/05_forms.md:185
msgid "\"<input> should be mounted\""
msgstr ""

#: src/view/05_forms.md:186
msgid ""
"// `leptos::HtmlElement<html::Input>` implements `Deref`\n"
"        // to a `web_sys::HtmlInputElement`.\n"
"        // this means we can call`HtmlInputElement::value()`\n"
"        // to get the current value of the input\n"
msgstr ""

#: src/view/05_forms.md:195
msgid ""
"Our `on_submit` handler will access the input’s value and use it to call "
"`set_name.set()`. To access the DOM node stored in the `NodeRef`, we can "
"simply call it as a function (or using `.get()`). This will return "
"`Option<leptos::HtmlElement<html::Input>>`, but we know that the element has "
"already been mounted (how else did you fire this event!), so it's safe to "
"unwrap here."
msgstr ""

#: src/view/05_forms.md:201
msgid ""
"We can then call `.value()` to get the value out of the input, because "
"`NodeRef` gives us access to a correctly-typed HTML element."
msgstr ""

#: src/view/05_forms.md:204
msgid ""
"Take a look at [`web_sys` and `HtmlElement`](../web_sys.md) to learn more "
"about using a `leptos::HtmlElement`. Also, see the full CodeSandbox example "
"at the end of this page."
msgstr ""

#: src/view/05_forms.md:207
msgid "Special Cases: `<textarea>` and `<select>`"
msgstr ""

#: src/view/05_forms.md:209
msgid "Two form elements tend to cause some confusion in different ways."
msgstr ""

#: src/view/05_forms.md:211
msgid "`<textarea>`"
msgstr ""

#: src/view/05_forms.md:213
msgid ""
"Unlike `<input>`, the `<textarea>` element does not support a `value` "
"attribute in HTML. Instead, it receives its initial value as a plain text "
"node in its HTML children."
msgstr ""

#: src/view/05_forms.md:216
msgid ""
"So if you’d like to server render an initial value, and have the value also "
"react in the browser, you can both pass it an initial text node as a child "
"and use `prop:value` to set its current value."
msgstr ""

#: src/view/05_forms.md:231
msgid "`<select>`"
msgstr ""

#: src/view/05_forms.md:233
msgid ""
"The `<select>` element can likewise be controlled via a `value` property on "
"the `<select>` itself, which will select whichever `<option>` has that value."
msgstr ""

